["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Gwilym Cradock was born before 1463 as the son of Ieuan Ap Caradog. He had at least 1 son with Gwenllian Melyn."},"et":{"before 1463–":"enne 1463–Surnud","1463–Male":"1463–Surnud","1400–Female":"1400–Surnud","1403–Male":"1403–Surnud","1330–Male":"1330–Surnud","1403":"1403","1400":"1400","before 1463":"enne 1463","1463":"1463","1330":"1330"},"fi":{"before 1463–":"ennen vuotta 1463–Kuollut","1463–Male":"1463–Kuollut","1400–Female":"1400–Kuollut","1403–Male":"1403–Kuollut","1330–Male":"1330–Kuollut","1403":"1403","1400":"1400","before 1463":"ennen vuotta 1463","1463":"1463","1330":"1330"},"fr":{"before 1463–":"avant 1463–Décédé","1463–Male":"1463–Décédé","1400–Female":"1400–Décédée","1403–Male":"1403–Décédé","1330–Male":"1330–Décédé","1403":"1403","1400":"1400","before 1463":"avant 1463","1463":"1463","1330":"1330","lifeSummary":"Gwilym Cradock est né avant 1463, fils de Ieuan Ap Caradog. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Gwenllian Melyn."},"de":{"before 1463–":"vor 1463–Verstorben","1463–Male":"1463–Verstorben","1400–Female":"1400–Verstorben","1403–Male":"1403–Verstorben","1330–Male":"1330–Verstorben","1403":"1403","1400":"1400","before 1463":"vor 1463","1463":"1463","1330":"1330","lifeSummary":"Gwilym Cradock wurde vor 1463, als Sohn von Ieuan Ap Caradog geboren. Er hatte mit Gwenllian Melyn mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"before 1463–":"before 1463–D